properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Wollongong education precinct - WOLLONGONG Princes Motorway, Memorial Drive at University of Wollongong
properties.adviceB: Plan your journey; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a u-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists accessing the M1 Northbound onramp at Northfields Avenue via Irvine St may be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road if traffic is congested.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow the instruction of traffic controllers.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Royal National Park -  Easter long weekend - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Princes Hwy at McKell Ave and Farnell Ave
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is expected to be busy over the Easter long weekend from Friday 2 to Monday 5 April.

Road closures will be in place as precincts and car parks reach capacity including Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena.

When parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave in Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr in Otford will close. Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave in Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

  • Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach
  • Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
  • Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
  • Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Royal National Park -  Easter long weekend

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Easter long weekend & holiday period - SHOALHAVEN Booderee Ave, Illowra Lane at Hyams Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions including a new roundabout under traffic control at the intersection of Booderee Avenue and Illowra Lane, speed reductions will be in place to manage the heavy traffic over the Easter period from 1 April to 18 April. 

A speed reduction from 80km/h to 40km/h will be in effect along Booderee Ave in both directions.

If Hyams Beach reaches capacity, or in the event of a catastrophic fire danger rating, temporary closures at Booderee Ave may be implemented. 

Motorists should arrive early or expect significant delays on roads approaching the township and beach during this period.  

Alternative white sand beaches can be found at Shoalhaven – South Coast NSW.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Easter long weekend & holiday period
